news.title: Ludhiana: LIT awaits fixation of reserve price for e-auction of properties
news.para: The LIT has sent a list of properties to the deputy commissioner for rate fixation. The reserve price for properties of other improvement trusts will also be fixed shortly as local bodies minister Balkar Singh has issued instructions in this regard.

news.title: New system to check illegal land use in Meerut
news.para: For the system being developed for the Meerut Development Authority, a common portal will be provided for all digital solutions, modules and interface between administration and the citizens.

news.title: Jawaharlal Nehru port authority earns over Rs 400 crore from leasing out 14 SEZ plots
news.para: Meanwhile, JNPA has issued Letter of Intent (LoI) towards the allotment of 14 plots to 14 successful bidders, including leading industries such as Welspun One and Fine Organics.

news.title: BBMP seals off 500-600 commercial properties; operations to continue
news.para: As of Saturday, BBMP special commissioner Munish Moudgil said 500-600 commercial properties have been sealed off.

news.title: Master plan for Kochi gets council nod
news.para: The corporation had published a draft master plan in April this year seeking the opinion of the public. It received 173 comments from the public and including these suggestions the master plan has been amended.

news.title: BBMP can't probe complaints on encroachment, says Karnataka HC
news.para: “The BBMP will have jurisdiction to investigate whether the construction is in accordance with the plan sanction, which can be done without reference to any particular encroachment of the property,” Justice Suraj Govindaraj said.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA seals flats of builder to recover sum paid by buyers
news.para: The complaint in this matter was filed in RERA in May 2022, with the complainants stating that they had purchased a flat near D-Mart in Jagatpura in 2014 and the builders—Vishal Sharma and Naveen Hiramandani—had promised to complete the project and give possession of the flat by April 2018.

news.title: Polish builder Murapol climbs 15% in first Warsaw IPO in two years
news.para: Murapol priced its IPO at 33 zlotys per share, giving it a valuation of 1.35 billion zlotys ($344.48 million), and Friday's debut at 37.50 zlotys, boosted that to 1.53 billion.

news.title: Blackstone-backed Sponda Oy agrees loan extension
news.para: Under the agreement Sponda, which was acquired by private equity group Blackstone Inc in 2017, secured an extension until February 2027.

news.title: Canadian housing starts dive as higher rates bite
news.para: The seasonally adjusted annualized rate of housing starts fell to 212,624 units from a downwardly revised 272,264 units in October, the Canadian Mortgage and Housing Corporation (CMHC) said.

news.title: Goa housing board to e-auction three commercial plots
news.para: The area of these plots is 1,526 sqm, 3,828 sqm and 2,247 sqm, respectively. The GHB has invited online applications for the disposal of these commercial plots by e-auction on outright sale.

news.title: Noida-Ghaziabad blue line metro proposal gets a boost with fund-sharing plan
news.para: The extension will see the Dwarka Sector 21-Noida Electronic City corridor being extended across the Delhi-Meerut Expressway via Indirapuram and Vaishali to Sahibabad in Ghaziabad.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 3,400 properties over tax default
news.para: According to a statement by the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC), 546 properties were sealed in the North West zone, 460 in South West zone, 415 in South zone, 403 in Central, and 341 properties in the North zone areas of the city.

news.title: Highrises will be inspected every two years to ensure compliance with safety rules: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: Fadnavis said highrise structures must incorporate refuge areas every two to three floors to provide residents shelter during fires as per the new building code.

news.title: Enforcement directorate registers PMLA case against Varanasi's Vinayak Group
news.para: Accounts of Vinayak Groups have also been freezed, ED sources said and added that hawala transactions were also reported which will be scrutinised by the central agency.

news.title: Owners in Chandigarh to take out rally against ban on certain categories of transfer of properties
news.para: “The objective of the rally is to alert the authorities to implement the Supreme Court’s order in Chandigarh in “true letter and spirit”, thereby, providing relief to the owners/co-owners of residential property share owners in Chandigarh,” said Kamal Gupta, a city-based property consultant.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Civic bodies to auction 21 plots, target Rs 3,000 crore
news.para: ​The priciest plot, owned by SRFDCL and located on the western stretch of the Sabarmati Riverfront, has a base price of Rs 3.68 lakh per sq m.

news.title: Gunthewari scheme fails to gather pace in Pune
news.para: According to PMC officials, around 1 lakh properties, including those in 34 merged areas, are probable beneficiaries of this scheme, which aims to regularise unauthorised properties.

news.title: Increased service charges to be waived for 56 Mhada colonies: Maharashtra housing minister
news.para: This means a sum of Rs 380 crores will be waived, benefiting 50,000 residents. The service charge had been increased between 1998 and 2021 but this had not been implemented.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers garners Rs 120 crore from anchor investors ahead of IPO
news.para: The company has allotted 33.33 lakh equity shares to 11 anchor investors at Rs 360 apiece, which is also the upper end of the price band, according to a circular uploaded on the BSE website.
